verses.verse: Hear <WH8085> my cry, <WH7440> God. <WH430> Listen <WH7181> to my prayer. <WH8605>
From the end <WH7097> of the earth, <WH776> I will call <WH7121> to you, <WH3820> when my heart is overwhelmed. <WH5848> Lead <WH5148> me to the rock <WH6697> that is higher than I. <WH7311>
For you have been a refuge <WH4268> for me, <WH5797> a strong tower <WH4026> from <WH6440> the enemy. <WH341>
I will dwell <WH1481> in your tent <WH168> forever. <WH5769> I will take refuge <WH2620> in the shelter <WH5643> of your wings. <WH3671> Selah. <WH5542>
For you, <WH430> God, have heard <WH8085> my vows. <WH5088> You have given <WH5414> me the heritage <WH3425> of those who fear <WH3373> your name. <WH8034>
You will prolong <WH3254> the king <WH4428>'s life; <WH3117> his years <WH8141> shall be for <WH1755> generations. <WH1755>
He shall be enthroned <WH3427> in <WH6440> God <WH430>'s presence <WH6440> forever. <WH5769> Appoint your loving kindness <WH2617> and truth, <WH571> that they may preserve him. <WH5341>
So I will sing <WH2167> praise to your name <WH8034> forever, <WH5703> that I may fulfill <WH7999> my vows <WH5088> daily. <WH3117>
